1
00:00:09,733 --> 00:00:11,333
How did the job interview go?

2
00:00:11,467 --> 00:00:12,767
Did you get it, sweetheart?

3
00:00:12,900 --> 00:00:14,300
Sorry, Ms. Castillo.

4
00:00:14,433 --> 00:00:18,567
We'll give you a call
once we finish our verification.

5
00:00:18,700 --> 00:00:20,000
They were actually
really impressed with me.

6
00:00:20,133 --> 00:00:21,167
Let's just keep this between us.

7
00:00:21,300 --> 00:00:22,267
I don't want any hassle.

8
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:25,667
I just have one small favor
to ask.

9
00:00:25,800 --> 00:00:27,767
Get your answers straight,
Edward.

10
00:00:27,900 --> 00:00:29,567
Don't embarrass this family.

11
00:00:29,700 --> 00:00:31,633
Or better yet, just don't talk.

12
00:00:31,767 --> 00:00:33,033
I came here to tell you

13
00:00:33,167 --> 00:00:34,867
I'm meeting
Mr. and Mrs. Sutherland later.

14
00:00:35,033 --> 00:00:36,867
I can do this.
You just need to trust me.

15
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:38,833
He needs to close this deal.

16
00:00:38,967 --> 00:00:40,133
Otherwise, bye-bye.

17
00:00:40,267 --> 00:00:43,267
It's beautiful, no doubt.
But it's just not for us.

18
00:00:44,500 --> 00:00:45,933
She's Bisaya.

19
00:00:46,067 --> 00:00:47,200
Oh, yeah. And you?

20
00:00:47,333 --> 00:00:50,033
Your new agent is really
impressive and charming.

21
00:00:50,167 --> 00:00:51,433
Don't let her go.

22
00:00:51,567 --> 00:00:53,500
Yes. It seems like
she can be a great asset

23
00:00:53,633 --> 00:00:55,833
to the company and to me.

24
00:00:57,133 --> 00:00:59,467
Marj, I'm heading out.

25
00:00:59,600 --> 00:01:01,400
Okay, Mikee. Take care.

26
00:01:01,533 --> 00:01:02,367
You, too.

27
00:01:02,500 --> 00:01:04,000
Bye!

28
00:01:10,667 --> 00:01:11,633
Marj?

29
00:01:12,667 --> 00:01:15,233
Sir! Do you need something?

30
00:01:15,367 --> 00:01:17,367
I'm about to leave.

31
00:01:17,500 --> 00:01:18,500
No.

32
00:01:20,133 --> 00:01:23,133
I'm wondering
if you'd like to go out.

33
00:01:23,267 --> 00:01:24,633
Let's have dinner.

34
00:01:25,800 --> 00:01:28,433
To celebrate
our great teamwork earlier.

35
00:01:29,967 --> 00:01:32,333
Sir, that's really kind,
but you don't have to.

36
00:01:32,467 --> 00:01:35,967
I'm just happy I got
to work with you.

37
00:01:36,100 --> 00:01:38,267
Same here.

38
00:01:39,633 --> 00:01:41,367
That's why...

39
00:01:41,533 --> 00:01:45,067
I want to thank you by treating
you to something.

40
00:01:45,200 --> 00:01:46,967
No saying no, okay?

41
00:01:48,767 --> 00:01:50,000
It's just...

42
00:01:50,133 --> 00:01:52,833
my mom and brother are
waiting for me at home.

43
00:01:54,233 --> 00:01:56,367
It won't take long.

44
00:01:56,500 --> 00:01:59,433
And you've been working
really hard since you got here.

45
00:01:59,567 --> 00:02:02,467
Sometimes, you have
to reward yourself,

46
00:02:02,600 --> 00:02:03,800
even if it's just a little.

47
00:02:09,267 --> 00:02:13,500
Sir Edward, this place
looks really expensive.

48
00:02:14,567 --> 00:02:17,133
I wish I'd dressed better.

49
00:02:17,267 --> 00:02:18,933
Marj, relax.

50
00:02:19,067 --> 00:02:20,000
Don't be self-conscious.

51
00:02:20,133 --> 00:02:24,200
And please, stop calling me sir.

52
00:02:24,333 --> 00:02:25,900
I'm not the boss.

53
00:02:26,033 --> 00:02:28,633
Paolo is.

54
00:02:28,767 --> 00:02:30,000
Not me.

55
00:02:30,133 --> 00:02:31,867
So...

56
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:33,733
just call me Edward.

57
00:02:35,467 --> 00:02:37,467
Okay...

58
00:02:37,600 --> 00:02:39,667
Edward.

59
00:02:39,800 --> 00:02:41,133
Better.

60
00:02:45,267 --> 00:02:46,667
Let's eat.

61
00:02:50,167 --> 00:02:52,233
- Thank you.
- Thanks.

62
00:02:52,367 --> 00:02:55,733
Glad we closed that deal
earlier, right?

63
00:02:55,867 --> 00:02:58,833
And we even convinced
Mr. Sutherland

64
00:02:58,967 --> 00:03:01,933
to let our company sell
their other properties.

65
00:03:03,700 --> 00:03:05,900
Honestly,

66
00:03:06,033 --> 00:03:08,533
if you hadn't helped me earlier,

67
00:03:08,667 --> 00:03:10,000
I probably...

68
00:03:11,300 --> 00:03:13,033
would've messed it up again.

69
00:03:15,167 --> 00:03:17,400
I was just doing my job.

70
00:03:18,667 --> 00:03:20,400
No need to thank me.

71
00:03:20,567 --> 00:03:23,067
It's a team effort.

72
00:03:23,200 --> 00:03:25,867
No, I really want to.

73
00:03:27,233 --> 00:03:30,400
You probably don't realize this,

74
00:03:30,533 --> 00:03:32,267
but this deal means a lot to me.

75
00:03:32,400 --> 00:03:37,767
Now I can finally prove to my
dad that I can deliver results.

76
00:03:37,900 --> 00:03:41,700
And for you, you get to
prove to Paolo that...

77
00:03:41,833 --> 00:03:42,867
hiring you

78
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:45,200
and giving you a second chance
was the right call.

79
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:04,500
You don't like the food?

80
00:04:04,633 --> 00:04:07,833
Want to order something else?
You're barely eating.

81
00:04:07,967 --> 00:04:09,600
- Excuse me...
- No, no, it's okay.

82
00:04:09,733 --> 00:04:11,433
It's really good.

83
00:04:11,567 --> 00:04:13,733
You're barely eating.

84
00:04:15,533 --> 00:04:17,700
I just wanted to
take some home.

85
00:04:17,833 --> 00:04:21,000
For my mom and my brother.

86
00:04:21,133 --> 00:04:23,367
I know they'll love it.

87
00:04:31,200 --> 00:04:34,900
Your family's always
on your mind wherever you are.

88
00:04:36,233 --> 00:04:37,133
Of course.

89
00:04:37,267 --> 00:04:39,800
They're the reason
I work so hard.

90
00:04:39,933 --> 00:04:44,133
So I want to share even
small wins with them.

91
00:04:44,267 --> 00:04:45,967
Even if it's just
a simple takeout.

92
00:04:49,300 --> 00:04:50,967
Eat.

93
00:04:51,100 --> 00:04:52,400
Eat that.

94
00:04:52,533 --> 00:04:54,567
I'll just order another
one for your family.

95
00:04:54,700 --> 00:04:56,700
No, it's really okay.

96
00:04:56,833 --> 00:04:58,000
It's fine.

97
00:04:58,133 --> 00:04:59,133
I insist.

98
00:05:00,333 --> 00:05:02,000
Go on.

99
00:05:02,167 --> 00:05:03,200
Eat it.

100
00:06:04,100 --> 00:06:06,600
Mom! Have you eaten?

101
00:06:06,733 --> 00:06:08,600
I have something for you.

102
00:06:13,200 --> 00:06:15,000
Here, here.

103
00:06:15,133 --> 00:06:17,267
There you go.

104
00:06:17,400 --> 00:06:18,733
- Sit down, sis.
- Sit down?

105
00:06:18,867 --> 00:06:21,833
You're so sweet.

106
00:06:23,967 --> 00:06:25,167
I'll take this off.

107
00:06:28,033 --> 00:06:30,033
So sweet!

108
00:06:30,167 --> 00:06:31,567
Love you, Jobert.

109
00:06:31,700 --> 00:06:33,067
Thank you.

110
00:06:34,233 --> 00:06:35,100
Yes.

111
00:06:35,233 --> 00:06:36,967
How are you?

112
00:06:37,100 --> 00:06:39,367
- Just relax.
- I love you.

113
00:06:40,900 --> 00:06:43,600
I want you to relax.

114
00:06:43,767 --> 00:06:46,533
You're tired from work.

115
00:06:46,667 --> 00:06:49,033
Thank you.

116
00:06:49,167 --> 00:06:51,633
Look at you,
smiling like that.

117
00:06:51,767 --> 00:06:54,767
Looks like you enjoyed
your date with Sir Edward.

118
00:06:54,900 --> 00:06:56,633
It wasn't a date!

119
00:06:56,767 --> 00:06:58,433
Edward and I
were just celebrating

120
00:06:58,567 --> 00:07:01,533
a big account we closed.

121
00:07:01,667 --> 00:07:03,267
First-name basis now?

122
00:07:03,400 --> 00:07:04,433
Get your mind out of the gutter!

123
00:07:04,567 --> 00:07:05,767
Wait.

124
00:07:07,200 --> 00:07:09,233
Wait, Marj.

125
00:07:09,367 --> 00:07:12,133
Is he different from your boss?

126
00:07:12,267 --> 00:07:13,467
Mom...

127
00:07:14,567 --> 00:07:18,333
he's Sir Paolo's brother.
They're totally different.

128
00:07:18,467 --> 00:07:22,067
Edward is generous
and approachable.

129
00:07:22,200 --> 00:07:25,967
Paolo's kind of cocky.

130
00:07:26,100 --> 00:07:29,567
So you like
the younger one better?

131
00:07:29,700 --> 00:07:32,567
I don't like either of them.
You're so silly.

132
00:07:32,700 --> 00:07:36,933
Work is my priority right now.
Love life's not.

133
00:07:37,067 --> 00:07:38,267
And...

134
00:07:38,400 --> 00:07:42,067
especialy after what happened
with Randall.

135
00:07:42,200 --> 00:07:45,067
I'm the only one
you love, sis.

136
00:07:45,200 --> 00:07:46,933
I'm the only one you love?

137
00:07:47,067 --> 00:07:48,633
You love me?

138
00:07:50,467 --> 00:07:51,867
You love your sister?

139
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:53,667
I love Jobert.

140
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:56,100
I love you.

141
00:07:56,233 --> 00:07:58,767
I love you, sis.

142
00:08:02,467 --> 00:08:04,267
I love you, too.

143
00:08:04,400 --> 00:08:07,567
Go on. Try the food.

144
00:08:07,700 --> 00:08:09,067
It's so good. It's good.

145
00:08:09,200 --> 00:08:11,167
- Come on. Sit down.
- Thank you, Marj.

146
00:08:11,300 --> 00:08:13,500
Go on, get Pong.

147
00:08:13,633 --> 00:08:15,433
Come on, Jobert. Sit here.

148
00:08:23,767 --> 00:08:26,300
Sir! Why are you half-naked?

149
00:08:26,433 --> 00:08:29,200
Sorry, I came straight
from my morning shot.

150
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:33,933
Wait, Miss. Did I offend you?

151
00:08:34,067 --> 00:08:36,667
No, I'm sorry.

152
00:08:36,800 --> 00:08:39,700
Gemma said I could come in.

153
00:08:39,833 --> 00:08:41,967
I'll just come back, Sir.

154
00:08:42,100 --> 00:08:44,167
No, it's fine.

155
00:08:44,300 --> 00:08:45,333
I'm almost done.

156
00:09:05,367 --> 00:09:07,567
You can turn around now,
Miss Tough Girl.

157
00:09:08,767 --> 00:09:10,733
Sir, why did you call me here?

158
00:09:10,867 --> 00:09:12,933
What do you need me to do?

159
00:09:13,067 --> 00:09:14,433
It's freezing in here.

160
00:09:14,567 --> 00:09:16,367
Why does it seem like
you're sweating?

161
00:09:17,733 --> 00:09:18,800
I'm not.

162
00:09:23,633 --> 00:09:26,933
Anyway, I'm assigning
you a new project.

163
00:09:27,067 --> 00:09:29,200
Mr. Valderama is looking
for a house for his daughter,

164
00:09:29,367 --> 00:09:31,167
who's getting married.

165
00:09:32,300 --> 00:09:36,000
Got it, Sir. I'll prepare a list
of properties.

166
00:09:36,133 --> 00:09:37,400
Just a heads-up.

167
00:09:37,533 --> 00:09:40,633
He's my dad's old
college friend.

168
00:09:40,767 --> 00:09:41,967
Okay?

169
00:09:42,100 --> 00:09:44,233
He's done a lot
for this company.

170
00:09:44,367 --> 00:09:46,667
Don't screw this up.

171
00:09:46,800 --> 00:09:49,467
Prove to me that last time
wasn't just luck.

172
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:51,433
You got that?

173
00:09:51,567 --> 00:09:53,967
Don't worry. I'll do my best.

174
00:10:10,500 --> 00:10:11,867
This Antipolo house

175
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:15,467
offers stunning city
and mountain views.

176
00:10:15,600 --> 00:10:18,067
And this open-plan house

177
00:10:18,200 --> 00:10:21,867
is great for entertaining family
and friends.

178
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:24,367
It also has an infinity pool,
Sir.

179
00:10:27,033 --> 00:10:30,533
The next one that I'll show
you...

180
00:10:31,267 --> 00:10:33,000
this is the Tagaytay house.

181
00:10:33,133 --> 00:10:36,167
Fully furnished
with bespoke designs,

182
00:10:36,333 --> 00:10:40,800
from the marble counters
to the lighting.

183
00:10:40,933 --> 00:10:45,733
Perfect as a wedding gift
for your future son-in-law.

184
00:11:08,633 --> 00:11:10,267
Morning.

185
00:11:10,400 --> 00:11:11,467
You.

186
00:11:11,600 --> 00:11:12,633
Sir?

187
00:11:12,767 --> 00:11:13,933
What are you wearing?

188
00:11:15,833 --> 00:11:17,700
How are you supposed
to close a deal

189
00:11:17,833 --> 00:11:20,333
looking like an old maid
in that long skirt?

190
00:11:20,467 --> 00:11:21,933
Fix yourself.

191
00:11:22,067 --> 00:11:23,400
Go!

192
00:11:27,100 --> 00:11:28,467
Hon?

193
00:11:29,833 --> 00:11:32,100
About closing the sale...

194
00:11:33,100 --> 00:11:36,567
aren't you going
tocongratulate Edward?

195
00:11:36,700 --> 00:11:39,633
He convinced Mr. Sutherland
to buy the property.

196
00:11:39,767 --> 00:11:41,000
That's not all, Hon.

197
00:11:41,167 --> 00:11:42,667
He also secured a partnership

198
00:11:42,800 --> 00:11:47,433
that makes us
their exclusive realtor.

199
00:11:47,567 --> 00:11:50,633
Does he want me
to give him a medal?

200
00:11:50,767 --> 00:11:54,333
If I praise him too much,
he might get complacent again.

201
00:11:56,133 --> 00:11:57,900
Guess I can't do anything right.

202
00:11:59,700 --> 00:12:00,533
Paolo.

203
00:12:00,667 --> 00:12:02,600
- Yes, Dad?
- Harry called this morning.

204
00:12:02,733 --> 00:12:04,500
He wants to buy
another property.

205
00:12:04,633 --> 00:12:08,033
He's already in the conference
room with one of our agents.

206
00:12:08,167 --> 00:12:09,433
Let's go.

207
00:12:26,967 --> 00:12:29,667
Sir, did you see anything
you liked?

208
00:12:29,800 --> 00:12:32,133
We'll talk about the
properties later.

209
00:12:33,167 --> 00:12:34,900
There's something else I want.

210
00:12:35,033 --> 00:12:38,067
Excuse me, I just need
to grab something upstairs.

211
00:12:38,200 --> 00:12:39,500
Pervert!

212
00:12:44,900 --> 00:12:46,400
What the hell is going on?

213
00:12:58,933 --> 00:13:00,533
What kind of employee is this,
Greg?

214
00:13:01,833 --> 00:13:04,233
I came here to do business,

215
00:13:04,367 --> 00:13:05,933
not to be assaulted!

216
00:13:06,067 --> 00:13:07,367
Wait,

217
00:13:07,500 --> 00:13:09,033
don't turn this around on me.

218
00:13:09,167 --> 00:13:11,767
I wouldn't have done anything
if you hadn't disrespected me!

219
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:16,067
Sir Paolo, please believe me.

220
00:13:16,200 --> 00:13:17,800
I was just defending myself.

221
00:13:17,933 --> 00:13:19,533
That's enough!

222
00:13:19,667 --> 00:13:21,867
Show some respect
for Mr. Valderama.

223
00:13:22,033 --> 00:13:23,733
He's a VIP client.

224
00:13:23,867 --> 00:13:25,200
Apologize to him. Now.

225
00:13:27,533 --> 00:13:30,267
Why should I apologize?

226
00:13:30,400 --> 00:13:32,067
I'm the one
who was disrespected.

227
00:13:32,200 --> 00:13:34,800
He should be the one
apologizing to me!

228
00:13:41,900 --> 00:13:44,167
Do you have any idea
what you've done?

229
00:13:44,300 --> 00:13:45,500
You're just a newbie here,

230
00:13:45,633 --> 00:13:47,233
and you're already
causing trouble.

231
00:13:47,367 --> 00:13:50,000
We could lose
one of our biggest clients!

232
00:13:51,967 --> 00:13:54,833
Dad. Dad, relax.

233
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:56,600
I'll handle Mr. Valderama.

234
00:13:56,733 --> 00:13:58,000
I'll take him to the men's club.

235
00:13:58,133 --> 00:14:00,300
I'm sure the women
there will make him forget

236
00:14:00,433 --> 00:14:01,467
what happened earlier.

237
00:14:02,967 --> 00:14:05,000
Talk to your new agent.

238
00:14:06,900 --> 00:14:08,300
Dad...

239
00:14:08,433 --> 00:14:11,167
let's hear Marj out first.

240
00:14:11,300 --> 00:14:15,067
There has to be a reason
she reacted that way.

241
00:14:15,200 --> 00:14:16,167
It doesn't matter!

242
00:14:17,900 --> 00:14:21,267
In this business,
the client is king.

243
00:14:21,400 --> 00:14:24,433
She has no right to disrespect
or hurt Mr. Valderama.

244
00:14:26,233 --> 00:14:28,733
Sir, I'm the victim here.

245
00:14:32,400 --> 00:14:35,700
Is that how little you value
your employees?

246
00:14:35,833 --> 00:14:39,167
Even when we're harassed
and abused,

247
00:14:39,300 --> 00:14:41,400
the client still matters more?

248
00:14:48,833 --> 00:14:50,733
See that?

249
00:14:50,867 --> 00:14:52,600
She's talking back!

250
00:14:52,733 --> 00:14:55,667
I've had enough of
your insubordination!

251
00:14:55,800 --> 00:14:57,067
Get your things.

252
00:14:57,200 --> 00:14:59,933
Get out of here
because you're fired!

253
00:15:00,067 --> 00:15:01,300
You're fired!

254
00:15:11,767 --> 00:15:13,500
Why am I getting
the punishment?

255
00:15:16,100 --> 00:15:18,200
I'm the one who got
sexually assaulted.

256
00:15:18,333 --> 00:15:20,967
Shouldn't you be
protecting me?

257
00:15:21,100 --> 00:15:22,633
Defending me?

258
00:15:22,767 --> 00:15:25,433
Why are you firing me instead?

259
00:15:25,567 --> 00:15:28,367
Dad, Marj is a good agent.

260
00:15:28,500 --> 00:15:30,967
She helped me
land the Sutherland account.

261
00:15:31,100 --> 00:15:33,567
You can't just fire her
like this.

262
00:15:33,700 --> 00:15:35,900
I didn't ask for your opinion!

263
00:15:37,233 --> 00:15:39,000
You all saw
how she talked back to me.

264
00:15:39,133 --> 00:15:41,200
She disrespected
my authority.

265
00:15:41,333 --> 00:15:42,533
That's why she has to go!

266
00:15:42,667 --> 00:15:44,400
Paolo, aren't you
going to do something?

267
00:15:44,533 --> 00:15:46,600
Dad's wrong!
Aren't you going to stop him?

268
00:15:46,733 --> 00:15:48,700
- What?
- Don't speak for me!

269
00:15:48,833 --> 00:15:50,667
- Stop it.
- That's enough!

270
00:15:50,800 --> 00:15:52,900
Your bickering
won't help, please.

271
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:57,100
Stop questioning
my decision.

272
00:15:57,233 --> 00:16:01,867
Last I checked, I still
own and run this company.

273
00:16:02,000 --> 00:16:04,433
So my word stands.

274
00:16:04,567 --> 00:16:06,533
You no longer work here.

275
00:16:06,667 --> 00:16:07,933
Leave.

276
00:16:08,900 --> 00:16:10,967
You don't have to throw me out.

277
00:16:13,100 --> 00:16:15,567
I quit.

278
00:16:15,700 --> 00:16:17,800
I refuse to be part
of a company

279
00:16:17,933 --> 00:16:20,633
that treats its employees
this unfairly.

280
00:16:56,867 --> 00:16:58,267
I'm sorry about what my dad did.

281
00:16:58,400 --> 00:17:01,200
I just want you to
know I believe you.

282
00:17:01,333 --> 00:17:03,367
I know you're the victim here.

283
00:17:03,500 --> 00:17:05,000
Thank you, Edward.

284
00:17:06,267 --> 00:17:09,500
It really means a lot
that you believe me.

285
00:17:11,633 --> 00:17:13,367
But there's nothing
we can do now.

286
00:17:13,500 --> 00:17:17,300
Your dad already wrote me off.

287
00:17:17,467 --> 00:17:19,533
Marj, I wish...

288
00:17:19,667 --> 00:17:23,300
I wish there was something
I could do to fix this.

289
00:17:23,433 --> 00:17:24,633
No.

290
00:17:24,767 --> 00:17:26,367
It's okay.

291
00:17:26,500 --> 00:17:29,967
I don't want to be the
reason you and Sir Greg fight.

292
00:17:31,300 --> 00:17:33,767
I'll just go.

293
00:17:33,900 --> 00:17:35,600
I don't want any
more trouble.

294
00:17:46,767 --> 00:17:48,200
We should've filed charges

295
00:17:48,367 --> 00:17:50,967
against the man
who harassed you.

296
00:17:51,100 --> 00:17:53,467
And dragged your
boss into it, too.

297
00:17:53,600 --> 00:17:58,100
All he did was tolerate sexual
harassment in that office.

298
00:17:58,233 --> 00:18:01,033
Mom, please. Let it go.

299
00:18:01,167 --> 00:18:04,133
He's a powerful man.

300
00:18:04,267 --> 00:18:06,700
And how would we even
pay for a lawyer?

301
00:18:06,833 --> 00:18:09,333
I don't have money.
I don't even have a job anymore.

302
00:18:10,800 --> 00:18:12,367
Let it go.

303
00:18:12,500 --> 00:18:14,167
Mom...

304
00:18:14,300 --> 00:18:16,000
I want to apologize to you.

305
00:18:17,133 --> 00:18:18,200
I'm sorry.

306
00:18:20,833 --> 00:18:22,500
Why are you apologizing?

307
00:18:22,667 --> 00:18:25,267
I'm embarrassed.

308
00:18:26,767 --> 00:18:30,233
Everything I do...

309
00:18:30,367 --> 00:18:31,633
just turns into a mess.

310
00:18:31,767 --> 00:18:35,767
I couldn't give you the
good life I promised.

311
00:18:35,900 --> 00:18:37,900
And our dream house. So...

312
00:18:39,967 --> 00:18:40,700
I'm sorry, Mom.

313
00:18:42,467 --> 00:18:44,300
Oh, sweetheart.

314
00:18:44,433 --> 00:18:45,800
Enough with the apologies.

315
00:18:47,233 --> 00:18:49,333
You've done nothing wrong.

316
00:18:50,067 --> 00:18:52,300
All your life,
you've done nothing

317
00:18:52,433 --> 00:18:54,267
but take care of our family.

318
00:18:58,400 --> 00:19:03,233
Don't blame yourself for things
you can't control.

319
00:19:07,033 --> 00:19:07,967
I'm sorry, Mom.

320
00:19:08,567 --> 00:19:10,167
That's enough.

321
00:19:10,300 --> 00:19:12,733
My heart hurts
seeing you like this.

322
00:19:26,667 --> 00:19:30,867
I don't want to see
my sister sad.

323
00:19:31,600 --> 00:19:33,400
I don't want to see her crying.

324
00:19:34,167 --> 00:19:34,833
No...

325
00:19:38,200 --> 00:19:42,500
I must think of a way.

326
00:19:44,333 --> 00:19:45,367
Poor sister...

327
00:19:49,133 --> 00:19:50,300
Poor Marj...

328
00:19:51,167 --> 00:19:51,733
Don't worry, Mom.

329
00:19:52,633 --> 00:19:53,933
You know I'm strong.

330
00:19:54,067 --> 00:19:54,867
Don't worry.

331
00:19:55,700 --> 00:19:56,600
Enough drama.

332
00:19:56,733 --> 00:19:59,233
I'll start looking
for a job tomorrow.

333
00:19:59,367 --> 00:19:59,867
Me, too.

334
00:20:00,833 --> 00:20:02,367
I'll look for work.

335
00:20:03,333 --> 00:20:05,100
No, Mom. Please don't.

336
00:20:05,500 --> 00:20:06,333
I don't want you getting tired.

337
00:20:06,467 --> 00:20:07,433
Just stay home.

338
00:20:07,567 --> 00:20:09,367
Take care of Jobert.

339
00:20:09,500 --> 00:20:10,900
Watch him closely.

340
00:20:11,033 --> 00:20:12,200
Poor Marj...

341
00:20:13,567 --> 00:20:14,533
Sis...

342
00:20:33,567 --> 00:20:34,367
Jobert!

343
00:20:52,900 --> 00:20:53,500
Jobert?

344
00:20:54,600 --> 00:20:56,233
Jobert!

345
00:20:56,367 --> 00:20:58,133
- Wake up, Jobert!
- Oh my God!

346
00:20:58,267 --> 00:20:58,733
Jobert!

347
00:21:00,367 --> 00:21:00,933
Jobert!

348
00:21:01,500 --> 00:21:03,033
Mom, stay here!

349
00:21:03,167 --> 00:21:03,900
I'm going to get help!

350
00:21:08,300 --> 00:21:09,567
Jobert!

351
00:21:11,167 --> 00:21:12,333
- Jobert!
- Jobert!

352
00:21:12,467 --> 00:21:13,733
Jobert!

353
00:21:13,867 --> 00:21:14,833
Jobert! Jobert!

354
00:21:15,633 --> 00:21:17,467
Wake up, my baby!

355
00:21:17,600 --> 00:21:18,300
Jobert!

356
00:21:18,433 --> 00:21:19,633
Jobert, wake up!

357
00:21:19,767 --> 00:21:20,233
Jobert!

358
00:21:20,367 --> 00:21:21,733
Jobert!

359
00:21:21,867 --> 00:21:23,100
- Please wake up!
- Jobert!

360
00:21:23,233 --> 00:21:23,933
Jobert!

361
00:21:24,067 --> 00:21:24,933
Jobert!

362
00:21:26,133 --> 00:21:28,600
He hit his head,
and he's not waking up!

363
00:21:29,267 --> 00:21:30,800
- Jobert, my child!
- I'm sorry, Ma'am.

364
00:21:30,933 --> 00:21:31,600
You're not allowed inside.

365
00:21:31,733 --> 00:21:32,633
Ma'am, please, wait.

366
00:21:32,767 --> 00:21:35,000
My brother's not used
to being away from us!

367
00:21:35,400 --> 00:21:37,367
I'm really sorry,
but we can't let you in.

368
00:21:37,500 --> 00:21:38,600
We'll take care of him.

369
00:21:48,167 --> 00:21:49,200
Marj...

370
00:21:51,667 --> 00:21:53,067
Jobert!

371
00:21:59,800 --> 00:22:01,667
Are you the relatives
of Jobert Castillo?

372
00:22:01,800 --> 00:22:04,800
Yes. Yes. How is my son?

373
00:22:04,933 --> 00:22:08,567
He's stable for now,
but we found head trauma.

374
00:22:08,700 --> 00:22:10,933
He may have gotten it
during the seizure.

375
00:22:11,633 --> 00:22:12,767
There's bleeding
inside the skull.

376
00:22:14,100 --> 00:22:16,833
Does that mean my
brother needs surgery?

377
00:22:17,633 --> 00:22:18,667
You're right.

378
00:22:18,800 --> 00:22:22,200
He needs emergency surgery to
relieve the pressure

379
00:22:22,333 --> 00:22:24,500
and prevent serious
brain damage.

380
00:22:26,733 --> 00:22:27,867
How much will it cost?

381
00:22:28,600 --> 00:22:30,900
Around two to three
hundred thousand pesos.

382
00:22:31,033 --> 00:22:32,833
That doesn't include
the medication yet.

383
00:22:35,767 --> 00:22:36,833
I'll give you some time.

384
00:22:44,200 --> 00:22:45,067
It's okay, Mom. It's okay.

385
00:22:58,567 --> 00:22:59,333
Jobert...

386
00:23:02,433 --> 00:23:03,267
Jobert...

387
00:23:05,433 --> 00:23:07,333
if you can hear
your sister and me,

388
00:23:08,867 --> 00:23:14,200
we just want you to know how
much we love you.

389
00:23:17,533 --> 00:23:20,067
Please be strong, Jobert.

390
00:23:22,500 --> 00:23:24,100
Don't give up.

391
00:23:28,300 --> 00:23:29,467
Don't let go, my child.

392
00:23:31,967 --> 00:23:35,567
We won't survive without you.

393
00:23:40,867 --> 00:23:42,200
Jobert, your sister is here.

394
00:23:44,400 --> 00:23:45,733
I won't leave you.

395
00:23:48,867 --> 00:23:51,433
We're still going to live
in our dream house, right?

396
00:23:52,700 --> 00:23:55,567
We'll still travel
abroad with Mom.

397
00:24:06,733 --> 00:24:09,100
I love you.

398
00:24:28,467 --> 00:24:30,367
Jobert, wake up.

399
00:24:58,700 --> 00:25:00,033
Girl, girl.

400
00:25:00,167 --> 00:25:02,433
Here. Sorry, this is all
I can lend you.

401
00:25:02,600 --> 00:25:04,200
This is already a big help.

402
00:25:04,333 --> 00:25:05,033
Thank you.

403
00:25:05,167 --> 00:25:05,867
Yeah.

404
00:25:10,933 --> 00:25:12,133
These are the clothes.
I brought them.

405
00:25:16,933 --> 00:25:19,767
Marj, how are we supposed
to come up

406
00:25:19,900 --> 00:25:22,233
with three hundred thousand
pesos?

407
00:25:22,367 --> 00:25:23,467
That's three hundred thousand.

408
00:25:25,500 --> 00:25:28,300
The doctor said your brother
needs surgery right away.

409
00:25:28,433 --> 00:25:31,333
If not, he could end up
brain-dead.

410
00:25:33,100 --> 00:25:35,200
I don't know, Mom.

411
00:25:35,367 --> 00:25:37,500
I already called everyone
I could borrow from,

412
00:25:37,633 --> 00:25:38,633
but failed.

413
00:25:39,867 --> 00:25:41,133
Why don't you call Sir Edward?

414
00:25:41,967 --> 00:25:43,300
You two get along, right?

415
00:25:44,133 --> 00:25:45,733
The Torrecampos
are insanely rich.

416
00:25:45,867 --> 00:25:47,433
Three hundred thousand
is nothing to them.

417
00:25:53,467 --> 00:25:54,233
Good evening.

418
00:25:54,900 --> 00:25:56,100
My name is Marjorie.

419
00:25:56,233 --> 00:25:58,300
I work for Torrecampo.

420
00:26:00,133 --> 00:26:02,767
I'm hoping to speak
with Sir Edward.

421
00:26:04,133 --> 00:26:05,167
It's really important.

422
00:26:06,033 --> 00:26:08,233
Oh, he's not here.

423
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:10,300
Sir Edward's in Iloilo.

424
00:26:11,433 --> 00:26:15,167
He's attending some
kind of convention.

425
00:26:15,900 --> 00:26:17,900
He won't be back until Tuesday.

426
00:26:21,133 --> 00:26:21,933
Thank you.

427
00:26:39,000 --> 00:26:40,267
What are you doing here?

428
00:26:41,700 --> 00:26:42,867
Didn't I already fire you?

429
00:26:43,833 --> 00:26:44,900
Right?

430
00:26:50,500 --> 00:26:53,367
Everyone seems so afraid
of Sir Greg.

431
00:26:53,500 --> 00:26:54,967
- No!
- The Torrecampos

432
00:26:55,100 --> 00:26:56,067
are hiding so many secrets.

433
00:26:56,200 --> 00:26:58,800
If this gets out,
it'll destroy us.

434
00:26:58,933 --> 00:27:00,233
It'll destroy the business.

435
00:27:00,367 --> 00:27:04,767
They're just hiding it
to protect their family image.

436
00:27:04,900 --> 00:27:06,800
The last thing we
need is a scandal.

437
00:27:06,933 --> 00:27:08,767
The patient needs surgery now.

438
00:27:08,900 --> 00:27:12,633
Otherwise, he could fall
into a coma or die.

439
00:27:12,767 --> 00:27:17,033
Even if you beg,
my answer is still no.

440
00:27:17,200 --> 00:27:19,633
Sir Greg, please.
I'm begging you.
